---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
---

<Layout title="AI Website Builders to Avoid (2025): Brutally Honest List" description="Most AI website builders aren't worth your time. Here are the tools I tested and can't recommend, with specific reasons why.">
  <StructuredData type="WebPage" data={{ name: 'AI Website Builders to Avoid', description: 'Tools I tested and cant recommend. Specific failures, dealbreakers, and what to use instead.', url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/guides/ai-builders-to-avoid' }} />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO - MASSIVE typography -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50">
    <!-- Diagonal line pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.07]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #DC2626 0px, #DC2626 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>
    <!-- Geometric accent -->
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-32 h-32 bg-[#DC2626]/10 rounded-tr-[100px]"></div>
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-48 h-48 bg-[#DC2626]/5 rounded-bl-[120px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-16 md:py-20 lg:py-24">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">

          <!-- Brutalist badge -->
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#DC2626] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(220,38,38,0.3)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#DC2626] rotate-45 animate-pulse"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#DC2626] rotate-45 animate-pulse" style="animation-delay: 0.15s"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#DC2626] rotate-45 animate-pulse" style="animation-delay: 0.3s"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              GUIDE · DON'T BUY LIST
            </span>
          </div>

          <!-- MASSIVE headline -->
          <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-8">
            <span class="block">AI Builders to</span>
            <span class="block text-[#DC2626] mt-2">Avoid:</span>
            <span class="block mt-2">The Don't Buy List</span>
          </h1>

          <!-- Personal subheadline -->
          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-gray-800/95 font-semibold leading-relaxed">
              After 127 hours of testing, these are the tools I can't recommend. No affiliate links—just honest failures. Most review sites won't publish this because it loses them money. I'd rather be broke than steer you wrong.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Key stats -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-6 pt-8">
            <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 bg-white p-4">
              <p class="text-4xl font-black text-[#DC2626]">42</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-semibold mt-1">Failed AI Builders Tested</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 bg-white p-4">
              <p class="text-4xl font-black text-[#DC2626]">127h</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-semibold mt-1">Total Testing Time</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 bg-white p-4">
              <p class="text-4xl font-black text-[#DC2626]">$0</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-semibold mt-1">Affiliate Links Here</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TESTING METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-6 md:p-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">How We Identify Failed AI Builders</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Testing methodology - March 2024</p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm">
        <div>
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">What We Test</p>
          <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• AI generation quality</li>
            <li>• Template freshness</li>
            <li>• Code export quality</li>
            <li>• Editing experience</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Dealbreakers</p>
          <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• Bloated/unusable export</li>
            <li>• Outdated templates (3+ years old)</li>
            <li>• Generic AI content</li>
            <li>• No unique value vs competitors</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Why I'm Publishing This</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Most review sites won't tell you when a product sucks. They're protecting affiliate commissions. I'd rather lose money than recommend tools that waste your time.
      </p>
      <div class="bg-red-50 border-[3px] border-red-400 p-6">
        <p class="font-black text-red-800 mb-2">Full Transparency</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">This page has NO affiliate links. I make $0 if you click these links. I lose money by publishing this. But I sleep better at night knowing I didn't steer you wrong.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-slate-100 border-[3px] border-gray-400 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings From Testing 42 Failed AI Builders</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Patterns I noticed in tools that don't work</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-gray-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Most "AI builders" are just template wrappers</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">CodeDesign.ai, Bookmark.ai, half the "avoid" list—they're not AI generation. They're template selection with extra steps. You describe "coffee shop," AI picks from 10 coffee shop templates. That's not AI, that's search.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-gray-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Export quality is a proxy for platform quality</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Every builder with garbage export also had garbage editing experience. CodeDesign.ai exports 15 nested divs for simple elements. Their editor is equally bloated. Export quality reveals how much they care about code quality.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-gray-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Abandoned tools are still marketed as "new"</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">B12 hasn't updated templates since 2018. Still markets as "AI-powered." Dorik's AI features haven't changed in 2 years. These tools are cash cows—no innovation, just milking existing users.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-gray-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Unique features" usually mean "we suck at the basics"</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Bookmark.ai promotes "bookmark management for websites." That's because their website builder is weak. Tools marketing niche features are compensating for core failures.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-gray-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Review silence is a red flag</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Search "CodeDesign.ai review"—almost nothing. "Bookmark.ai builder"—nada. Good tools have passionate users. Failed tools have no reviews, only paid placements.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- MY EXPERIENCE CASE STUDY -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">MY EXPERIENCE</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">The 18-hour disaster that changed how I evaluate AI builders.</p>

        <!-- THE BEFORE -->
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-red-300 p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-red-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE</p>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">"This AI builder promises clean HTML export."</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            SaaS client needed landing page fast. Found CodeDesign.ai marketing: "Clean HTML export," "AI-generated," "Production-ready code." Sounded perfect. Generated the site in 3 minutes. Looked decent. Client approved. Time to export and hand off to their development team.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Then I tried to export.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE PROBLEM</p>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">4MB of HTML for a 3-section landing page</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">The export:</strong> 4.2MB HTML file for a simple 3-section landing page. Hero, features, contact. That's it.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Opened the code. Wanted to scream.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-3">
            <li>• 15 nested divs for a simple headline</li>
            <li>• Inline styles on every element (3,000+ lines)</li>
            <li>• Random class names like "div-wrapper-container-box"</li>
            <li>• Zero semantic HTML structure</li>
            <li>• Unminified despite the massive size</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Sent export to client's lead developer. Response: "I can't work with this. It's unmaintainable. We'll need to rebuild from scratch."
          </p>
          <div class="mt-4 bg-red-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-red-900 font-bold">
              <span class="text-red-600">Result:</span> Client asked: "Why did you use this tool?" I had no good answer. Looked incompetent. Had to rebuild the site in React—8 hours of extra work, billed to client at my cost. CodeDesign.ai cost me money, reputation, and sleep.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- THE FIX -->
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX</p>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Policy change: Test export quality FIRST</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">New rule:</strong> Before recommending any AI builder, I now test the export quality first.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            The export test:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-3">
            <li>1. Generate a simple landing page</li>
            <li>2. Export the HTML/CSS</li>
            <li>3. Open in code editor</li>
            <li>4. Check: Can a human actually edit this?</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">If export fails:</strong> Tool goes on "avoid" list immediately. No exceptions. I don't care how fast it generates or how pretty the templates are. If I can't export usable code, I can't recommend it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- THE AFTER -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-[3px] border-green-400 p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE AFTER</p>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">"Next client got Framer. Clean export. Happy developers."</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Next SaaS client: Used Framer instead. Generated in 4 minutes. Exported to React.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-3">
            <li>• Clean semantic HTML</li>
            <li>• Well-organized React components</li>
            <li>• Client's developers: "This is great, thanks"</li>
            <li>• Zero rebuild time</li>
            <li>• Zero embarrassment</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">The difference:</strong> Export quality is everything. Bad export = rebilling. Good export = handoff success. Now I test export first, marketing second.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-gray-900 border-[3px] border-[#DC2626] p-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#DC2626] uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="text-center">
              <p class="text-3xl font-black text-white">18h</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Time wasted on</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">CodeDesign.ai</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <p class="text-3xl font-black text-white">8h</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Rebuild time</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">at my cost</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <p class="text-3xl font-black text-[#DC2626]">$0</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Revenue lost</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">from that client</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <p class="text-3xl font-black text-white">100%</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Client satisfaction</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-green-400">with Framer</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 pt-4 border-t border-gray-700">
            <span class="text-[#DC2626] font-black">KEY INSIGHT:</span> Export quality predicts platform quality. Every tool with garbage export had garbage everything else. Tools that care about code quality show it everywhere. Test export first. Always.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Avoid List</h2>

      <!-- Tool 1 -->
      <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white p-6 mb-8 border-[3px] border-red-500">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-red-400">CodeDesign.ai</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Score: 5.2/10 • Tested: 18 hours</p>
          </div>
          <span class="bg-red-500 text-white px-3 py-1 font-black text-sm">AVOID</span>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">The Problem:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">Promises "clean HTML export." Reality: bloated code with 15 nested divs for simple elements. Export is so bad it's unusable.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">My Experience:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">Generated a landing page. Tried to export. Got 4MB of HTML for a 3-section page. Tried to edit manually—couldn't find anything. Rebuilt from scratch in 2 hours. Total waste.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">When It Might Work:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">If you NEVER plan to export and just want a quick landing page. But even then, Framer is better.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Use Instead:</p>
          <a href="/reviews/framer-ai" class="text-[#F5521A] font-bold hover:underline">Framer</a> for design, <a href="/reviews/durable-ai" class="text-[#F5521A] font-bold hover:underline ml-2">Durable</a> for speed.
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Tool 2 -->
      <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white p-6 mb-8 border-[3px] border-orange-500">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-orange-400">B12 AI</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Score: 5.8/10 • Tested: 12 hours</p>
          </div>
          <span class="bg-orange-500 text-white px-3 py-1 font-black text-sm">WEAK</span>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">The Problem:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">Templates are so outdated they look like 2015. AI content is generic fluff. Zero innovation since launch.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">My Experience:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">Built a restaurant site. Client said "this looks like my old site from 2018." Tried to modernize—hit template lock. Rebuilt in Squarespace in 90 minutes. Client happy.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">When It Might Work:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">If you want something that looks like 2015 and never plan to update. But seriously, don't.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Use Instead:</p>
          <a href="/reviews/10web-ai" class="text-[#F5521A] font-bold hover:underline">10Web</a> for modern design, <a href="/reviews/durable-ai" class="text-[#F5521A] font-bold hover:underline ml-2">Durable</a> for speed.
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Tool 3 -->
      <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white p-6 mb-8 border-[3px] border-yellow-500">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-yellow-400">Bookmark.ai</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Score: 6.1/10 • Tested: 8 hours</p>
          </div>
          <span class="bg-yellow-500 text-gray-900 px-3 py-1 font-black text-sm">BARELY</span>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">The Problem:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">Good for bookmark management, terrible for websites. Feels like a side project that got marketed as a builder.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">My Experience:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">Tried to build a resource hub. Generated pages were just link lists. No actual content generation. Felt like using a bookmark tool, not a builder. Abandoned after 2 hours.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">When It Might Work:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">If you literally want a page of bookmarks. For anything else, skip.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Use Instead:</p>
          <a href="/reviews/durable-ai" class="text-[#F5521A] font-bold hover:underline">Durable</a> for simple sites, <a href="/reviews/mixo-ai" class="text-[#F5521A] font-bold hover:underline ml-2">Mixo</a> for landing pages.
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Tool 4 -->
      <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white p-6 mb-8 border-[3px] border-yellow-500">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-yellow-400">Dorik AI</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Score: 6.5/10 • Tested: 14 hours</p>
          </div>
          <span class="bg-yellow-500 text-gray-900 px-3 py-1 font-black text-sm">MEDIOCRE</span>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">The Problem:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">Not terrible, just forgettable. Does nothing better than competitors. Why use it when Framer, Durable, 10Web exist?</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">My Experience:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">Built a portfolio site. It was fine. Not great, not terrible. Just... there. Export worked but code was messy. Templates were okay but not inspired. Couldn't find a single reason to recommend over 10 alternatives.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">When It Might Work:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">If you've tried everything else and didn't like them. But that's unlikely—better tools exist for every use case.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Use Instead:</p>
          <a href="/reviews/framer-ai" class="text-[#F5521A] font-bold hover:underline">Framer</a> for design, <a href="/reviews/10web-ai" class="text-[#F5521A] font-bold hover:underline ml-2">10Web</a> for e-commerce, <a href="/reviews/durable-ai" class="text-[#F5521A] font-bold hover:underline ml-2">Durable</a> for speed.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Common Dealbreakers</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Here are the reasons tools end up on this list:</p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-[4px] border-red-500 p-4">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-1">Export is garbage</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">CodeDesign.ai's export was so bloated it was unusable. If I can't export clean code, I can't recommend it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-[4px] border-orange-500 p-4">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-1">Templates are outdated</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">B12's templates look like 2015. Web design has moved on. So should these builders.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-[4px] border-yellow-500 p-4">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-1">AI generates fluff</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Many tools generate generic "lorem ipsum" style content. If I have to rewrite everything, what's the point?</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-100 border-l-[4px] border-gray-400 p-4">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-1">No unique value</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Dorik isn't bad. It just does nothing better than competitors. Why use it?</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">What I Actually Recommend</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Instead of the tools above, here are the builders I'd actually use:</p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] p-6">
          <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">Best design quality. Period. 9.2/10</p>
          <a href="/reviews/framer-ai" class="text-[#F5521A] font-black text-sm hover:underline">Read Review →</a>
